        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I play a necro becuase I like the class. I chose it as my fourth class after trying a Warrior, then a Paladin, then a Mage. By the time I settled on necro I knew the capabilities of most classes and chose necro becuase the class ablities appealed to me.</P><P>Since then I've played my necro almost exclusively. But something concerns me with my encounters of a lot of necros. They strike me as being horribly selfish in their goals and the most troubling thing about this is that they assume that every other necro matches their thought processes.</P><P>Take an incident last night for instance. I habitually collect the spells I consider most important for our class that I know are uncommon. This means I save them when they drop and I also purchase them when I see them going at a reasonable price. Then during my downtime I chat to other necros of appropriate level and if they need the spells I sell them to them at my cost. All I ask is that they take the time out to come to me to get the spells.</P><P>Last night I sent a tell to a 53 necro asking if he needed Convergence and Augmentation of bones. He said that he did so I told him the price was 1k. I paid 500pp for each spell - zero profit there at all. He then harangued me for about 20 minutes accusing me of being a money grubbing .... I explained exactly what I was doing but he just would not shut up.</P><P>Frankly this is not the first time this kind of b/s has happened to me but I've pretty much decided it will be the last time.</P><P>I was 51 before I got my 49 pet, after submitting to a sacrifice to get the Aquisition Beza words. I really didn't want any other necro to go thru that, thus my saving words and spells.</P><P>But since it really seems that the majority of other necros are generally selfish sob's I am not going to be doing this anymore. Rare necro words drop for me now and they are being sold to vendors - the same deal with spells.</P><P>I wonder why people always look a gift horse in the mouth? Well this particular horses mouth is now closed.</P><P> </font></td>
